1. Web
    - It is a portion of Internet with restricted access.
    - Tim Berner Lee
    - Standards maintained  W3C & WHATWG.

	www.w3.org
	http://whatwg.org

2. Web Server
    - Server resembles both hardware and software.
    - Server satisfies the client request by sending and receving data.
    - Its responsibility is to
	a) Handle request from client
	b) Process the request
	c) Generate a response for client request
	d) Send response to client

    - Servers are 2 types
	a) Local Web Server
		- Apache Tomcat, IIS 
	b) Cloud Server
		- aws, azure, firebase, git

		  Web Server on Windows PC		
		  ======================
	           [Internet Information Services Manager]

Locate Web Server on Windows PC:
============================
1. Open windows "Control Panel"
2. Switch to "Icons View"
3. Go to "Administrative Tools"
4. Look for "Internet Information Services Manager" [IIS]

How to add IIS into Windows PC?
=========================
1. Open Control Panel
2. Go to "Programs and Features"
3. Click on "Turn Windows Features ON or OFF".
4. Select "Internet Information Services"
5. Click OK


Test the WebServer:
================
1. Open any browser : Chrome, Edge, FireFox, Opera, Safari etc..
2. Type the following in address bar

	http://127.0.0.1
	        (or)
	http://localhost

3. Web Site
    - Web site is a virtual directory on Web Server.
	   site  = location
    - It comprises of resources, which are served to client on request.

	  http://127.0.0.1/netflix	Virtual Path
	  D:\netflix			Physical Path

Creating a new Website
==================
1. Open IIS    [ run -> inetmgr ]
2. Expand local computer
3. Expand "sites" folder
4. Right Click on "Default Website"
5. Add Virtual Directory
	Alias		: netflix
	Physical path	: d:\netflix

6. Go to Physical path and add folders
	- images
	       pic.jpg
	- docs
	       notes.pdf

     http://localhost/netflix/images/pic.jpg
     http://localhost/netflix/docs/notes.pdf

